Accounting and Performance in UK Higher Education - a grounded</gtr:title><gtr:status>Closed</gtr:status><gtr:grantCategory>Fellowship</gtr:grantCategory><gtr:grantReference>ES/E005292/1</gtr:grantReference><gtr:abstractText>&lt;p>The social, economic and political profile of Higher Education (HE) has never been higher. Significant pressures such as globalisation, massification and new technology, impact upon HE. Therefore, the need to understand approaches to strategic and financial management in higher education is urgent, both in conceptual terms and in the establishment and promotion of good practice. Previous study has addressed strategic management accounting (SMA) in the HE sector through developing a theoretical framework according to the ?grounded theory? methodology. The framework for this research is ranked around the core of the strategising mindset, and it is sought to undertake further limited research in order to test and extend these findings, in accordance with grounded theory principles. Furthermore, training courses in the field of qualitative and quantitative research methods will be undertaken, in particular to build up a statistical research profile. Conferences will be attended for dissemination of research and networking. The envisaged primary beneficiaries of this research will be accounting and HE management scholars, HE institutions, funding bodies and essentially government.&lt;/p></gtr:abstractText><gtr:fund><gtr:end>2008-05-31</gtr:end><gtr:funder url="http://gtr.ukri.org:80/organisation/924BE15C-91F2-4AAD-941A-3F338324B6AE"><gtr:id>924BE15C-91F2-4AAD-941A-3F338324B6AE</gtr:id><gtr:name>ESRC</gtr:name></gtr:funder><gtr:start>2007-06-01</gtr:start><gtr:type>INCOME_ACTUAL</gtr:type><gtr:valuePounds>65455</gtr:valuePounds></gtr:fund><gtr:output><gtr:artisticAndCreativeProductOutputs/><gtr:collaborationOutputs/><gtr:disseminationOutputs/><gtr:exploitationOutputs/><gtr:furtherFundingOutputs/><gtr:impactSummaryOutputs/><gtr:intellectualProper